<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.8367925>
    dc:description "Fig. 7. Sexual organs of selected Dina spp.; schematic drawings and photograph. A. Dina ratschaensis from Sakishore Cave (Georgia). B. Dina cf. ratschaensis Kobakhidze, 1958 from Western Georgia (unknown cave). C. Dina absoloni Johansson, 1913 from Brestice (Herzegovina). A, C. Dissected by Grosser. B. Dissected by Epshtein (in Lukin 1976: fig. 263a–d; length × width of dissected specimens. A. 50 × 9 mm. B. b1 38 × 5 mm, b2 50 × 6 mm. C. 30 × 6 mm. a = genital atrium; b = ovisacs; c = vas deferens; d = testisacs." ;
